title: The Surprising Adventures of the Magical Monarch of Mo and His People
creator: L. Frank Baum
description: LibriVox recording of The Surprising Adventures of the Magical Monarch of Mo and His People, by L. Frank Baum. The Magical Monarch of Mo is a set of stories about the titular king, his queen, and his royal children. The stories are uproariously funny, dealing with topics as absurd as a man losing his temper who then tries to find it, an evil midget who steals a princess's big toe, and an entire city filled with highly civilized monkeys! Join the Monarch and all his friends for a rollicking adventure, filled with fun for the whole family! (Summary by Miriam Esther Goldman) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; Children; Fairy tales; Fantasy; Humor; Short stories
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: This book is a treasure!!! Good readers, cute stories - Enjoyed it very much! Thanks!
The first four chapters are read at high speed in a monotonous monotone. Reader's heavy German accent is often difficult to understand. The succeeding readers are fine.
Both the stories and the readers are great! Thanks Libravox!
I could not understand the first few stories as the reader had a thick accent, which would have been ok except that she read very fast. Otherwise it was great.
